'''Keeto Thermoncy''' (born 29 March 2006) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for the U21 team of [[BSC Young Boys|Young Boys]] in the [[Promotion League]]. Born in Switzerland, he plays for the [[Haiti national football team|Haiti national team]].

==Club career==
Thermoncy is a youth product of [[FC Fribourg|Fribourg]], Team AFF-FFV and [[BSC Young Boys|Young Boys]].<ref name="auto">{{Cite web|url=https://www.laliberte.ch/articles/sports/football/ce-jeune-fribourgeois-a-ete-selectionne-en-equipe-nationale-d-haiti-1200499|title=Bientôt en Coupe du monde? Ce jeune footballeur fribourgeois a été sélectionné en équipe nationale d'Haïti|first=Pierre|last=Salinas|date=17 September 2025|website=La Liberté}}</ref> He was promoted to their U21 team in the [[Promotion League]] in 2023.<ref name="auto1">{{Cite web|url=https://sportpassioninfo.com/keeto-thermoncy-je-suis-pret-a-tout-donner-pour-haiti-avec-le-coeur/|title=Keeto Thermoncy : « Je suis prêt à tout donner pour Haïti, avec le cœur » - Sport Passion Info|date=8 July 2025}}</ref> He was registered for Young Boys' senior squad for the [[2025–26 UEFA Europa League]] campaign.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sportpassioninfo.com/keeto-thermoncy-de-la-suisse-a-haiti-il-multiplie-les-convocations/|title=Keeto Thermoncy : De la Suisse à Haïti, il multiplie les convocations - Sport Passion Info|date=4 September 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in Switzerland, Thermoncy was born to a Haitian father and Swiss mother and holds dual Swiss and Haitian citizenship.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sportpassioninfo.com/keeto-thermoncy-fait-un-grand-pas-vers-sa-nationalite-sportive/|title=Keeto Thermoncy fait un grand pas vers sa nationalité sportive - Sport Passion Info|date=6 July 2025}}</ref> He was first called up to the Swiss U14s, but the camp was cancelled due to the [[COVID-19 pandemic]].<ref name="auto1"/> He was called up to a training camp for the [[Haiti national under-17 football team|Haiti U17]]s in November 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.haitilibre.com/en/news-38195-haiti-world-u-17-peru-2023-start-of-the-selection-first-gathering-list-of-players.html|title=Haiti - World U-17 Peru 2023 : Start of the selection, first gathering (List of players) - HaitiLibre.com : Haiti news 7/7|website=HaitiLibre.com}}</ref> In June 2024, he was called up to the preliminary [[Haiti national under-20 football team|Haiti U20]]s for qualifiers for the [[2025 FIFA U-20 World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.haitilibre.com/en/news-42592-haiti-u-20-world-cup-qualifiers-chile-2025-grenadiers-pre-list-+-calendar.html|title=Haiti - U-20 World Cup Qualifiers Chile 2025 : Grenadiers pre-list (+ calendar) - HaitiLibre.com : Haiti news 7/7|website=HaitiLibre.com}}</ref>

He was called up to the [[Haiti national football team|Haiti senior national team]] for a set of [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification]] matches in October 2025.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://frapp.ch/fr/articles/stories/le-fribourgeois-keeto-thermoncy-dans-lequipe-dhaiti|title=Un Fribourgeois en sélection haïtienne pour la première fois|website=Frapp}}</ref> He won his first cap with Haiti on 9 October, featuring in a 3–0 win over [[Nicaragua national football team|Nicaragua]].<ref>https://www.haitilibre.com/en/news-45954-haiti-flash-2026-world-cup-qualifiers-haiti-beats-nicaragua-[3-0]-videos.html</ref>

==Personal life==
Keeto's younger brother, Wasson Thermoncy, is also a footballer and Haiti youth international.<ref name="auto"/>

